quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,141,"and so that Allah may purify those who believe and eradicate the disbelievers."
  3,142,"Do you think that you shall enter Paradise despite that Allah has not yet known those of you who carry out Jihad nor has He known those who are steadfast."
  3,143,"And you had been longing for death before you faced it. Now, you have seen it with your open eyes."
  3,144,"And Muhammad is but a messenger, there have been messengers before him. So, if he dies or is killed, would you turn back on your heels? And whoever turns back on his heels can never harm Allah at all. And Allah shall soon reward the grateful."
  3,145,"And it is not the choice of a person to die without the will of Allah, death being a time-bound destiny. And whoever seeks the return in this world, We shall give him out of it, and whoever seeks the return in the Hereafter, We shall give him out of it. And We shall soon reward the grateful."
  3,146,"And there has been a number of prophets along with whom have fought many men of Allah, and they did not lose heart for what they suffered in the way of Allah, nor did they become weak, nor did they yield. And Allah loves the steadfast."
  3,147,"And they had nothing else to say except that they said: 'Our Lord, forgive us our sins and our excesses in our conduct, make firm our feet and help us against the disbelieving people.'"
  3,148,"So, Allah gave them the return in this world and also the better rewards in the Hereafter. And Allah loves those who do good."